text:
The Medicaid cuts in President Trump’s “Big Beautiful Bill” will hit families with children with disabilities particularly hard.

In Westbrook, I visited Luminibility’s “Birth to Three” program, which provides essential early intervention services for children with disabilities, paid for by Medicaid. These services are now at risk under the President's bill, all so the ultra-wealthy can get a tax break. I’m fighting to reverse these cuts, protect services, and lower health care costs.

The Revolution Wind project went through nine years of permitting. The Department of Defense confirmed it has no adverse impact on national security. And now, a federal judge has resoundingly rejected the Trump Administration’s unjustified halt work order. It’s time to let the thousands of union workers finish the job.

This swift decision by a federal district court is a victory not just for the parties involved, but simple commonsense. 

A multi-billion project that is 80% complete and was fully permitted with input by the Pentagon is not a national security problem. The Department of the Interior should take the hint and let the thousands of construction workers finish the job.

The Trump Administration's indiscriminate cuts to medical research is impacting real patients right now, including Old Lyme's Sarah Craig. 

Sarah receives treatment for stage four lung cancer through NIH research programs. This week, she joined me to discuss the critical need to protect NIH funding.

Health care is heading for a crisis. Hospitals, doctors, & patient groups are warning us of looming costs. We just had the chance to protect patients & stabilize coverage, but the GOP majority chose to end longstanding insurance premium support in their partisan funding bill. https://t.co/EA80p40aqB

Happy 78th birthday to the U.S. Air Force! 

Since 1947, U.S. Airmen have ensured our national security in the air, space, and cyber domains. https://t.co/5LVFcTAlEa

Last week, Russia launched its largest drone attack on Ukraine since the start of its full-scale invasion and then flew drones into the airspace of two NATO allies – Poland & Romania.  

Also last week, I joined a bipartisan effort to block a totally misguided measure to cut off all military support to the brave freedom fighters of Ukraine. As I stated on the floor, they are holding the line not just for themselves, but for their allies in Europe. Slava Ukraini!

Today is National Voter Registration Day! Casting a vote and participating in our democracy is how we shape our nation’s future. 

Register to vote here: https://t.co/9uvmVHb80u 
And verify voter registration here: https://t.co/fdRgPXz9wQ https://t.co/RnRhN6LSQi

Congressman McCaul has been terrific partner as Co-Chair of the bipartisan Friends of Australia Caucus. As Chair of the Foreign Affairs Committee, he played a key role in passing AUKUS-enabling provisions. His commitment to public service & strong international alliances will be missed.

Australia’s massive commitment to submarine access in the Indo-Pacific for AUKUS allies is proof that AUKUS benefits all 3 nation’s Navies. 

There should be no doubt that AUKUS shall endure. https://t.co/Dg71yYDgtH

Thanks to the team at CT Community for Addiction Recovery for briefing me on their efforts to prevent overdoses in our region. They pioneered the lifesaving “recovery coaches” support model and have received federal assistance for their efforts. Now, the Trump Administration is slashing that assistance at the Department of Health and the "Big Beautiful Bill" is gutting Medicaid coverage that covers recovery treatment. These cuts will severely impact community efforts to prevent overdoses. It’s unacceptable. Congress must reverse them.

It was an honor to celebrate the USS Normandy’s presence at the Connecticut Maritime Heritage Festival. After 36 years in service, the Normandy is set for decommissioning later this month. Its name is sacred – it honors the sacrifice of over 7,500 GIs who were killed or wounded on D-Day 1944. Current and former crewmembers from throughout the ship’s history joined the ceremony at Fort Trumbull. A special day for the City of New London – a community which truly reveres U.S. Navy history.

With bipartisan support, we successfully blocked a measure that would have further delayed the Revolution Wind offshore wind energy project by requiring the Department of Defense to re-review the project — which has ALREADY been extensively reviewed and vetted by DoD.

The project is 80% complete, with thousands of jobs and lower energy costs for CT and RI hanging in the balance. The Trump Administration must lift its halt work order immediately.

Today marks 24 years since the September 11th, 2001 terror attacks. On this solemn day, we honor the 2,977 innocent lives lost and the bravery of first responders who rushed toward danger on the day and in the rescue, recovery, and relief effort. https://t.co/E6fKWflZlj
I’m horrified by the murder of Charlie Kirk. Political violence is never acceptable. I’m praying for his family during this heartbreaking time.

The Revolution Wind offshore wind energy project was extensively reviewed and vetted by the Department of Defense. Now, an amendment to the annual defense bill in Congress would require the project to be re-reviewed by DoD. This would prolong an unjustified halt work order by the Trump Administration while thousands of union jobs and a much-needed energy expansion for 350,000 homes hang in the balance. I spoke in strong opposition to this amendment.

Exciting to see the progress of the U.S. Coast Guard Museum construction! Great visit with union carpenters who are passionate about this project’s goal to honor the Coast Guard. With the huge crane on site, the first three decks of the museum structure are now framed in steel, with the fourth deck rising up.

The House Armed Services Committee passed the 2026 NDAA by a vote of 55-2. 

The men and women in uniform deserve no less than that bipartisan commitment to national security. 

The full House must pass our bipartisan bill and reject partisan amendments. https://t.co/olcmNbqhO4

Leaving an 80% complete offshore wind energy project in limbo is completely unacceptable. Hundreds of jobs and cheaper electricity for 350,000 homes in Connecticut & Rhode Island are on the line. 

The Trump Administration’s halt work order on the Revolution Wind project must be overturned.

Visited Allyson Angelini, the 2025 Outstanding Young Farmer of the year at her phenomenal Full Heart Farm in Ledyard. Rooftop solar was installed with USDA funds approved in 2024. She had to overcome a months-long freeze of solar programs by the new Administration, but she prevailed and is now saving thousands in electricity costs, that will keep Full Heart’s delicious specialty crops sustainable for years to come.

I had a good visit with the Electric Boat Metal Trades Council this morning and discussed the Navy submarine construction plans, AUKUS, and the wage improvement funding that Congress passed in 2024. That wage improvement has been included in the MTC labor contract. Thank you to President of the MTC Peter Baker and the almost 4,000 MTC members, who are the finest shipbuilders in the world, for all you do.

The Trump Administration’s unjustifiable halt work order on the Revolution Wind project is going to cause immediate and significant harm. The project is 80% complete! 

Given the hundreds of jobs on the line and the need for more energy supply to lower Connecticut energy costs, this lawsuit is well founded.

My colleague @Rep_Magaziner asked a simple question to a Trump Administration official to provide a reason for why they halted an 80% complete offshore wind energy project, putting hundreds of jobs at risk and squandering a much-needed energy supply expansion for CT & RI. 

Incredibly, he couldn’t give an answer.

Congress is finally back in session. At my town halls in CT, I heard people’s serious concerns about health care cuts & deficit increases in President Trump’s “Big Beautiful Bill”. 

We have a lot of work to do. At the top of the list should be listening to warnings from patients and hospitals and working to avoid the harm this ugly bill will create.

I just signed a discharge petition to force a vote on releasing the Epstein files. 

Speaker Johnson sent us home for an extremely long recess to avoid this vote. Now, we’re back, and we must delivery the transparency that Americans are asking for.

The Pentagon’s review of AUKUS is promised to be “an empirical and clear-eyed assessment of the initiative.” 

If that standard is applied, the review’s findings will show that AUKUS is the strongest, most effective plan for the U.S. to deter China’s malign behavior in the Indo-Pacific. 

Read my op-ed in @TheNatlInterest: https://t.co/dlN6nQGz55

Now, we must reinvest in the federal programs that power our training pipelines and support workers on the job. I’m fighting back against the Trump Administration's proposed cuts in funding to the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act and OSHA. We cannot let momentum stall.

Happy Labor Day! Eastern CT’s manufacturing sector is setting the standard for the nation. Our workforce training pipelines and “career pathways” curricula have connected thousands of students and job seekers to quality careers and higher education, and our labor unions are ensuring good pay and benefits through apprenticeships and collective bargaining.

A ruling which upholds what has been clear for months: President Trump doesn’t have the authority to impose his sweeping tariffs. 

Congress should pass the bipartisan Trade Review Act to end the price hikes Americans are facing under the President’s tariffs. https://t.co/gmfkRu57LI

Eastern CT shipbuilders are second to none. In Congress, we secured funding for a record pay raise to support their work.

From the Groton shipyard to sub suppliers & small businesses across our region, I’m focused on connecting people to not just jobs, but high-quality careers. https://t.co/fdCDw6xGLl

Local health care providers are facing the real consequences of the nearly $1 trillion in cuts to health care in President Trump’s “Big Beautiful Bill”.

I visited Vernon Rehabilitation and Healthcare Center to hear the harmful impacts of these cuts on patients, services, and staff.

The Trump Admin is claiming vague national security "concerns" to justify halting work on the Revolution Wind project that is 80% complete. 

Here are the facts. The Bureau of Ocean Energy Management already analyzed & resolved all national security issues for the project with the Coast Guard, Navy, & NORAD in a 2023 record of decision.

Last week, we celebrated Vernon history with the unveiling of a dazzling mural depicting some of the iconic scenes of the Rockville community. 

The mural was commissioned by Matt Hickey, owner of Tri Towne Lube & Repairs and brilliantly composed and painted by local mural artist Laura Costello. She wove together the Henry Park tower, the Keystone tunnel, and farm and factory sites well known to locals. Bravo!

This Trump Administration order to halt the Revolution Wind project cites national security concerns, but in 2023, the Bureau of Ocean Energy Management already analyzed and addressed national security concerns for the project with the Department of Defense.

By terminating this project that is 80% complete, the Trump administration is putting 200 jobs at risk and canceling a much-needed energy expansion for Connecticut. The worst way to protect the region’s economy, suppliers, workers, and energy.

The Rotary Club has a great mix of residents who really care about their community and nation. T

hank you to Jan Perruccio, Rotary Club President and former Superintendent of Old Saybrook Public Schools.

It was great to join the Old Saybrook Rotary Club yesterday. There was a big turnout of rotary members and also members from the nearby VFW post. 

We discussed veterans issues, the future of the U.S. Department of Education, job training for the EB shipyard, and the nutrition cuts at USDA.

Storrs and Adelaide are 10,000 miles apart, but they’re close partners under AUKUS. 

UConn & the University of Adelaide are collaborating to share UConn’s expertise in undersea vehicle technology with the “AUKUS Scholars” exchange program. It was great to visit the University of Adelaide last week, and Storrs today, to discuss how this research is driving AUKIS forward.

Thanks to everyone who joined my town hall today at Juniper Hill Village in Storrs. People are concerned about the Trump Administration's cuts to Medicaid and housing assistance programs. These are bedrock programs to meet people's needs. I won't stop fighting to protect them. https://t.co/gDNGo77AB0

It was an honor to meet with Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese as part of a bipartisan delegation in support of AUKUS. The U.S. and Australia are the closest of allies, and there is strong bipartisan support in Washington to make AUKUS a success.

Back home, Eastern Connecticut is driving AUKUS forward. From shipbuilding to submarine officer training and undersea research partnerships with UConn and Adelaide University, there was a lot of exciting news from CT-02 to share during our visit.

The funding is administered by @CRCOG1 and provides direct financial assistance to homeowners for repair costs not covered by CFSIC. 

In addition to this home in Manchester, more homeowners are set to receive support through this program in Enfield, Ellington, Coventry, Willington, and Bolton.

It was 10 years ago when the crumbling foundations crisis was brought to light. The work to deliver relief for CT homeowners continues. 

Today in Manchester, @RepJohnLarson and I joined the Capitol Region Council of Governments to mark the first home repaired for crumbling concrete foundations using federal Community Project funding I secured in the federal budget in 2022.

I had a great visit to Doncasters’ Groton facility, which employs about 210 workers. The aerospace manufacturer recently completed a major facility upgrade, adding 17,000 square feet of space. https://t.co/syRhi94Q9q

Social Security was created 90 years ago today. Americans pay into Social Security over the course of the working lives under the PROMISE that benefits will be there to support them in retirement. 

Now, the Trump Administration is attacking Social Security and degrading services while giving a tax break to billionaires. Congress must honor the promise made to Americans. Protect our checks!

Honored to join MDA-UAW Local 571 members in solidarity to celebrate their new hard fought 5-year contract with Electric Boat. The contract includes a record wage increase for Groton shipyard workers, which we secured funding for in Congress. Collective bargaining is rebuilding America’s defense industrial base!

President Trump’s “Big Beautiful Bill” failed to extend Affordable Care Act subsidies and sharply narrowed enrollment. As a result, the CT Insurance Department has warned that ACA premiums for many will increase as much as 75% next year. I’m a co-sponsor of the Health Care Affordability Act to avoid this disaster for millions of Americans. Congress must act.

CT Adjutant General Francis Evon’s selection as the new President of the Adjutants General Association of the United States, is a proud moment for the state of the Connecticut and the outstanding men and women of the CT Guard.

He is a fierce advocate for the enlisted reserve members all across the 50 states and territories of our country. He has earned the respect of his peers, because of his knowledge and experience as a guardsman and because they know he will lead this critical part of our national defense with integrity and patriotism. Congratulations General Evon!

https://t.co/6SGA72OJWP

President Trump has put a 50% tariff on Brazilian coffee, which U.S. agriculture can’t replace. That’s just one of many fruits, vegetables, and proteins that tariffs will increase costs on in the grocery store. I’m working across the aisle in Congress to stop the chaotic tariffs. https://t.co/7CXQvH9uSt

Big crowd at the Colchester Senior Center to observe the 90th anniversary of Social Security. We also discussed the real-life consequences of President Trump’s Medicaid and Medicare cuts in the “Big Beautiful Bill” for hospitals and patients.

There was strong agreement that Congress should protect Social Security from huge staff cuts at the Social Security Administration. These are bedrock programs that all Americans care about and rely on. Indiscriminately cutting them is a broken promise to Americans.

Great to join a strong gathering of submarine suppliers from across Connecticut in Norwich as part of the “Rising Tides” initiative to boost hiring in submarine jobs. The historic demand signal for submarine construction is creating good manufacturing careers across our state! https://t.co/WuRfJdWdiX

Steel is in the air at the future National Coast Guard Museum. 

I stopped by the construction site on the New London waterfront this week. John Metcalf (USCG Ret.) from the Museum Association updated me on the project. Construction is quickly moving forward with a new huge crane.

Health care services are stretched thin, and the $1 trillion in Medicaid & ACA cuts that President Trump signed into law will create huge new gaps in coverage. In Willimantic, Generations Health is working to close gaps in care with a new mobile health unit.

The van is critical in the sprawling eastern CT where the "tyranny of distance" makes access to health care particularly challenging. The operating costs of the van are covered with 2024 approved federal grant funds, which will maintain access to health care and dental services. Thanks to Generations CEO Missy Meyers and her team for their non-stop efforts to deliver care in the most rural part of our state.

Homelessness is a housing issue. But while he cuts housing support and expansion, President Trump just signed a new executive order to criminalize homelessness. I joined CT leaders to show support for our towns' hard work to prevent homelessness. We need to focus on root causes and support services — not undermine the work of local law enforcement & service providers.

Happy birthday to the U.S Coast Guard! The success of Coasties begins here in eastern CT at the U.S. Coast Guard Academy in New London. I will always support their mission as the world's premier maritime law enforcement agency. https://t.co/z4Qwp22Gio

The very conservative GOP economist Douglas Holtz-Eakin of the American Enterprise Institute is right — Trump’s firing of the statistics commissioner Erika McEntarfar is just “shooting the messenger.”

The public — including investors, employers, and workers — need professional, accurate data, not data designed to please the ego of a thin skinned, angry politician.

Medicaid and Medicare turn 60 years old today, when Lyndon Johnson and Congress dramatically expanded health care access for seniors and patients in need. President Trump promised to "love and cherish" these programs. However, those words ring hollow after he signed into law the largest Medicaid cut in U.S. history in a bill that will also trigger Medicare cuts by $500 billion. It will eliminate coverage for over 10 million Americans and put hospitals’ finances at serious risk. It is a violation of the promise that was made 60 years ago that I will fight to restore.

Firefighters’ brave work to keep us safe often puts them at risk of toxic chemical exposure. I worked with the Town of Lisbon to secure federal Community Project funding for uniform decontamination equipment at the new Lisbon Fire Station. Last week, I visited the station to catch up with Fire Chief Dave Gifford, his son, and First Selectman Tom Sparkman.

It was an honor to join servicemembers and their families at the CT National Guard send-off and “welcome home” ceremony at Bradley Air Base. 

The 242nd Engineering unit returned from Jordan and the 103rd Airlift and Air Control units are deploying for missions in Africa and the Middle East, part of the Guard’s wide-ranging security mission at home and abroad. Thank you to these servicemembers and their families for their service and sacrifice.

Glad to see Vernon’s senior center expansion project get underway. This is going to bring more programming with more space to stay healthy and active. And it’s made possible by $1.87M in federal funding passed by Congress and allocated to Vernon back in 2021. https://t.co/BJK8J9pR0e

In Chaplin, I joined First Selectman Juan Roman and the Public Works team at the ribbon cutting for the fully replaced England Road Bridge – 80% funded by the Infrastructure Law of 2021. Four years after Congress passed the Infrastructure Law, it continues to deliver for eastern CT.

The Israeli Government should stop the stonewalling of the U.N. aid delivery system and put U.N. experienced experts back in control to get help into Gaza ASAP, where famine conditions have set in. Their own military assessment verified the U.N. was effective at providing aid.

https://t.co/cds3AH9RF3

The small town of Scotland having SIX different ZIP Codes leads to serious consequences for residents. Mail deliveries, absentee ballots, and where to send kids to school are all thrown into confusion by the ZIP Code chaos. This week, the House passed my bill to mandate ONE ZIP Code for Scotland. I caught up with First Selectman Dana Barrow Jr. outside the Scotland Post Office.

Families across eastern CT are feeling the rising cost of food. Trump tariffs are projected to raise consumer costs even higher by over $200/month. 

From foods we don’t grow in the US – like coffee and bananas – to locally grown eastern CT produced with higher input costs, every step of the food supply chain is getting hit.

Today, Australia made a $500 million payment into the U.S. Submarine Industrial Base. This is the second installment of a total $3 BILLION investment to help us build more submarines. 

Unprecedented support from an ally. It's only happening because of AUKUS. 🇺🇸🇦🇺

Speaker Johnson just shut down the House for 6 weeks to avoid a simple vote on a bipartisan bill to release the Epstein files. 

Left undone: Preventing a shutdown, lowering costs, & securing our national defense. All are more important than protecting Epstein's black book. https://t.co/ob26hnrymb

Great news. My bill to mandate a single ZIP Code for Scotland has passed the House. Scotland residents face the serious consequences of having six ZIP Codes for a town of less than 1,600 people. It’s an inexcusable man-made issue that screams out for Congress to deliver a commonsense solution.

President Trump, Vice President Vance, & Attorney General Bondi have done a 180 degree turn on the Epstein files. This week, House Republicans tried to deflect with a do-nothing, non-biding resolution that does nothing to provide transparency. Pass a law. Release the Epstein files.

President Trump promised to “love and cherish” Medicaid. Well, he just signed into law the largest Medicaid cut in U.S. history – nearly $1 trillion. 

Not a lot of "love" for hospitals, seniors, and kids who will take the hit with loss of coverage. https://t.co/VH8Y9aMKjE
Really great to join Putnam Elks Community Day over the weekend. It was a special day to celebrate the Putnam Lodge of Elks 574’s 125th anniversary. https://t.co/IceOg9hHN7

Last weekend, I stopped by the under-construction CT National Guard Putnam Readiness Center to see its progress. 

It won’t be long before the new Readiness Center is a reality. This federally funded project will ensure that the Guard returns to the Quiet Corner! https://t.co/UqEVEildGx

The brutal killing of Palestinian-American Sayfollah Musallet must be met with justice and accountability. Settler violence in the West Bank continues to surge. 

I’m a co-sponsor of the West Bank Violence Prevention Act, which seeks to prevent settler violence and hold those who commit it accountable. To achieve lasting peace between Israelis and Palestinians, the U.S. must respond swiftly to settler violence.

Good news. The House Armed Services Committee just adopted my bipartisan amendment to close a funding gap for 2 Virginia-class submarines in the 2026 budget. A chaotic budget process left a huge shortfall for Virginia submarines. Our committee worked in a bipartisan fashion to clean it up. More work is ahead.

President Trump is trying to force American taxpayers to pay for his luxury Qatari plane. And his Administration isn’t even being transparent about the costs! We know that retrofitting a plane to be Air Force One costs into the BILLIONS. I filed an NDAA amendment to prohibit any funding for Trump’s Qatar Force One.

This year’s defense budget process has been messy & chaotic. The Trump Administration failed to provide a strategically-sound budget and inexplicably split funding into two vehicles: the base budget & the reconciliation bill. But once again, the Seapower Subcommittee overcame the challenge with bipartisan work to fill gaps & strengthen shipbuilding.

PFAS forever chemicals are a serious health risk to our communities. In Preston, farmer and town Selectman Jerry Grabarek has discovered high levels of PFAS in his blood. We met to discuss the long overdue federal response to forever chemical pollution. https://t.co/TA7Zia4ne7

We need an all of the above approach to lowering energy costs. The partisan GOP budget bill just sent us in the wrong direction by eliminating clean energy tax credits. 

I visited solar and battery business Earthlight Tech in Ellington to hear the impact of these cuts on CT. This bill will raise household energy costs & threaten 1.75 million jobs nationwide.

I had the honor of joining the Mashantucket Pequot Tribal Nation for the Fire Department Chief Anthony Saccone’s pinning ceremony – presided by Chairman Rodney Butler. 

Chief Saccone and I worked together for over a decade to secure Public Safety Officers benefits for our nation’s fire police. In 2021, our bill, the Protecting America’s Fire Responders Act, was signed into law. Southeastern CT is lucky to have Chief Saccone continuing to serve our community.

Eastern Connecticut and Australia may be 10,000 miles apart, but our partnership through AUKUS is ironclad and only getting stronger. 

I recently met virtually with UConn and a delegation from the University of Adelaide visiting Storrs. UConn’s National Institute for Undersea Vehicle Technology is leading research to advance the U.S. Navy’s future undersea fleet, and through this partnership, they’re sharing their expertise with our allies to make AUKUS a success.

Even as families across the country are struggling with rising food costs, the partisan GOP budget bill passed last week makes huge cuts to food assistance programs to pay for tax breaks for the rich. 

At Access Agency in Willimantic, which enrolls needy families in SNAP and runs a food pantry with donated items, the staff described how SNAP cuts and USDA cuts to food banks will increase food insecurity for local seniors and families with children.

President Trump promised that he would “love and cherish” Medicaid and Medicare. 

Now, he just signed into law the largest cut to Medicaid in U.S. history in a bill that is so fiscally irresponsible, it will also trigger a $500 billion cut to Medicare. All to give the rich a tax break. 

A flagrant violation of the American people’s trust.
A total blast to join the 40th annual Willimantic Boom Box Parade! A true grassroots patriotic tradition. https://t.co/PwWAJi2hwk

Wishing everyone in CT's 2nd District a happy & safe Independence Day! 249 years ago, our nation threw off King George III's autocratic rule, defining our national identity. 

Today & everyday, thank you to our servicemembers, military families, and veterans for bravely defending our freedom.

I voted NO on the largest health care cut in U.S. history, a tax giveaway for the rich, and a $3.4 trillion increase to the deficit. We have a golden opportunity to lower costs, grow the economy, & cut the debt. Instead, the GOP jammed through this reckless bill. Like any law, it can be overturned. The will of the majority will ensure it is.

Before heading back to DC yesterday, I visited the kids at Thames River Magnet School during lunchtime – powered by Groton Public Schools’ summer meals program. USDA funding makes free breakfast & lunch possible for these students. I’m fighting to protect food programs from cuts in the “Big Beautiful Bill”.

Back in DC to vote on the awful 900-page “Big Beautiful Bill”. I’m a BIG NO. 

The American people oppose this bill by a 2-1 margin. Keep making your voices heard! https://t.co/tgszRFDteW

The Senate just passed a 900-page megabill that will kick millions off their health care and force the hospitals we all rely on to close. 

All to pay for a permanent tax break for the top 1% AND still blow up the deficit by TRILLIONS. 

The fight now moves to the House to stop this bill. I will join the vast majority of Americans who detest this measure and vote NO.

The health care cuts in the "Big Beautiful Bill" are so massive that hospitals across Connecticut will be forced to scale back services for all patients.

I heard that from L+M Hospital in New London on the shoreline and now from Johnson Memorial Hospital in Stafford near the Massachusetts border. The story is the same – tens of thousands will lose their health coverage and we all will pay. This is the wrong direction for our country. We have to stop this bill.

This is great news for Waterford. This week, Electric Boat announced that it is acquiring the old Macy’s at Crystal Mall for new office space and 700 jobs. Amid record hiring rates at the Groton shipyard, this news really underscores the pivotal role southeastern Connecticut plays in delivering on the Navy’s and Congress’ long-term commitment to growing our submarine fleet.

This week, I met with the Connecticut Nurses Association, who earnestly stressed how much health care providers rely on strong federal Medicaid funding. As they bluntly stated, Medicaid pays for nurses. We must stop the massive Medicaid cuts in the misnamed “Big Beautiful Bill”. https://t.co/3JafAdGvOB

The Supreme Court’s decision to limit the reach of well established citizenship rights in the 14th Amendment of the Constitution to random federal district court geographic zones tramples on the principle of “equal justice under the law”, enshrined on the Supreme Court building. It is a decision that divides our nation’s people and weakens the union.

All sorts of ugly provisions are slithering out of the “Big Beautiful Bill” – including health care cuts that are so bad, hospitals will be forced to close. 

The House passed the bill in the DEAD OF NIGHT last month. Now, the Senate is making it even WORSE. We've got to block this ugly bill.

Mark Davis was a deeply respected, hardworking, and trusted reporter. He went above and beyond to invest himself in the issues and tell the story to the people of Connecticut. Mark will be missed by our state. I’m sending my deepest condolences to the Davis family and Mark's cheerful, talented colleague Joe Sferrazza.

Three years ago, the Supreme Court took away women's rights to make their own health care decisions. Now, millions of women live under extreme state abortion bans. 

Congress must pass the Women's Health Protection Act to restore reproductive rights nationwide.

Four-star Army General David Petraeus' famous 2003 maxim about the Iraq War, "tell me how this ends", should be at the forefront in the mind of every American, particularly President Trump, who hit Iran with military force without a declaration of war which the Constitution clearly requires. 

As our nation learned the hard way in Iraq and Afghanistan, it is easier to start a war in the Middle East, than to end one. As a member of the Armed Services Committee, I will be pushing to assert Congressional authority and oversight, particularly focused on force protection of U.S. servicemembers in the region, who are exposed to the highest risk of harm.

Captain Andrew Pedersen-Keel's Gold Star family from Madison has made a positive difference for veterans in need and kept the sacred memory of Capt. Pedersen-Keel's sacrifice alive after he was killed in action in Afghanistan in 2013. At this weekend's Travelers Championship in Cromwell, APK Charities, founded by Capt. Pedersen-Keel's parents Bob and Helen Pedersen-Keiser, is partnering with the tournament as part of the Birdies for Charity Initiative, which provides a 50 percent bonus on fundraising for local organizations. Kudos to Bob and Helen for their tireless work.

The cuts to Medicaid in the misnamed "One Big Beautiful Bill" are getting WORSE in the Senate version of the bill. I visited Lawrence + Memorial hospital in New London to hear how these cuts will impact services. 40% of L+M patients are covered by Medicaid.

As the American Hospital Association stated, these cuts will take health coverage away from millions nationwide and "strain emergency departments as they become the family doctor to millions of newly uninsured people... the proposal will force hospitals to reconsider services or potentially close." It's not fear mongering. L+M and hospitals all across the country are dumbfounded at these cuts. H.R. 1 needs to be stopped.

Juneteenth marks the end of slavery in the United States on June 19th, 1865. 

Today, we reflect on the courageous struggle to abolish slavery and look to the work ahead to make “a more perfect union” with freedom and justice for all. 

Wishing everyone in eastern Connecticut a happy Juneteenth!

At my town halls in eastern CT, people are seriously concerned about health care cuts in the so-called "One Big Beautiful Bill" H.R. 1. These cuts would take away health care for 15 million Americans & put our hospitals in dire financial straits. No wonder hospitals from all across the country are strongly opposed to this bill.

I am deeply saddened by the horrific targeted shootings of Minnesota state lawmakers Speaker Emerita Melissa Hortman, Senator John Hoffman, and their spouses. 

Political violence has no place in America. I am praying for them and their families during this heartbreaking time.

Law enforcement officers safeguarded our republic on January 6th, 2021. President Trump may have pardoned the violent criminals who attacked these brave officers, but we must never forget the truth, the facts, the history of what happened on that day. The plaque honors all the local, state, and federal departments that responded on the day of infamy. It’s up to all of us.

Secretary Hegseth, if you really care about strengthening shipbuilding, we need a real budget – not a pencil sketch plan that cuts shipbuilding by $17 billion compared to the last administration's budget. https://t.co/YlJXi7DUS7

Congratulations to Emma Rustichelli, Connecticut's 2nd District 2025 Congressional Art Competition winner! 

Emma is a junior at Woodstock Academy. Her work Pigne "Pinecones" is now on display with hundreds of other winners in the U.S. Capitol!

I met with a big group of Connecticut homebuilders to discuss how we can continue working together to build more homes in eastern Connecticut. All hardworking people should be able to afford a home, and when we increase supply, costs go down. https://t.co/FudVS1ZdaO

The Trump administration has the right to review AUKUS, but just like the UK’s own review found, AUKUS is overwhelmingly in the interest of all 3 nations and the entire Indo-Pacific. Abandoning AUKUS would cause lasting harm to our standing with close allies and rejoice in Beijing.

The passing of Congressman Raúl Grijalva is a loss that is felt all across our country, even in eastern Connecticut. In 2007, when I was the freshman Member of Connecticut’s Second District, Raúl managed passage in the U.S. House of Representatives of the Eight Mile River Wild and Scenic Designation bill that Senator Chris Dodd and I cosponsored and was signed into law by President George Bush. 

I will never forget how Raúl came to my assistance when the bill faced an unexpected partisan roadblock, and we worked together to secure its passage.

He was a tenacious warrior for protecting our national parks, natural monuments, and wild and scenic rivers, like the mighty Eight Mile River. We also sat side-by-side on the House Committee on Education and Labor for over a decade. He and I shared wonderful ‘sidebar’ jokes and comments, which he muttered at the same time he doodled intricate designs on his notepad during long, sometimes arduous, hearings.

He was a great Member of Congress and a great person. I extend my deepest condolences to Raúl’s family and hope their memories of him will be a blessing. I know my memory of him will always be a blessing for me.
